text: Alena Horalová (born 24 November 1952) is a Czech handball player, born in Plzeň. She played for the Czechoslovak national team, and represented Czechoslovakia at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:People from Plzeň Category:Czechoslovak female handball players Category:Olympic handball players of Czechoslovakia Category:Handball players at the 1980 Summer Olympics
